Detailed Description

The interface IRealFunction defines an interface of real valued function with one real argument.

This interface will typically be implemented for distributions. See MathNet.Numerics.Distributions.

double MathNet.Numerics.IRealFunction.ValueOf ( double  input  ) 

Gets the function value associated the provided input value.

The semantic associated to this interface is deterministic function (the same input should lead to the same returned value).

Implemented in MathNet.Numerics.Distributions.CumulativeNormalDistribution, and MathNet.Numerics.Distributions.InvCumulativeNormalDistribution.
